{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Simple triangular mesh in a given geometry\n",
    "\n",
    "This tutorial will show to generate 2d meshes withing a given geometry.\n",
    "\n",
    "At the very beginning, the necessary libraries have to be imported."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "from meshkernel import Mesh2dFactory, MeshKernel, GeometryList"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, using numpy library we will load data from Deltares custom polygon file \"test.pol\".\n",
    "Please note we ignore the first few rows in the file to skip some Deltares specific data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "polygonnp = np.loadtxt('data_examples/test.pol',comments='*', skiprows=8, dtype=np.double)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we will extract the data loaded from the file and save it as required by `MeshKernel`, in a `GeometryList`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_coordinates = np.array(polygonnp[:,0], dtype=np.double)\n",
    "y_coordinates = np.array(polygonnp[:,1], dtype=np.double)\n",
    "polygon = GeometryList(x_coordinates, y_coordinates)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Before we continue this is how the imported polygon looks like:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x25aba8a8580>]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.plot(x_coordinates, y_coordinates, \".-\", color=\"blue\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Then, we create a MeshKernel instance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mk = MeshKernel()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can now execute the `MeshKernel` function `mesh2d_make_mesh_from_polygon` to generate a tirangular mesh based on the given polygon."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mk.mesh2d_make_mesh_from_polygon(polygon)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Then, we retrieve the state from the `MeshKernel` instance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mesh2d_input = mk.mesh2d_get()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This is the grid that we have generated:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for edge_index in range(0, mesh2d_input.edge_nodes.size, 2):\n",
    "    first_edge_node_index = mesh2d_input.edge_nodes[edge_index]\n",
    "    second_edge_node_index = mesh2d_input.edge_nodes[edge_index + 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "    edge_x = [\n",
    "        mesh2d_input.node_x[first_edge_node_index],\n",
    "        mesh2d_input.node_x[second_edge_node_index],\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    edge_y = [\n",
    "        mesh2d_input.node_y[first_edge_node_index],\n",
    "        mesh2d_input.node_y[second_edge_node_index],\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.plot(edge_x, edge_y, color=\"black\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
